{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"When a required key is absent from both the file and the environment, the error message names the missing key by its exact config path (e.g., `database.host`).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure risk is in wiring: file load + `TOOL_` env overlay + required-key validation + startup error formatting. A pure unit test of only the validator can miss path-mapping/merge bugs that produce the wrong missing-key path.","test_description":"Use a temp config file that omits `database.host`, clear related `TOOL_` env vars, run startup loader entrypoint, assert it fails and error text includes exact `database.host` path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the environment variable `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is set, the loader resolves the config file path relative to that directory rather than `~/.config`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is env-var path resolution plus filesystem lookup. Mocking path resolution or fs can hide incorrect join/precedence behavior. No subprocess/network is required.","test_description":"Create temp dir structure under a fake `XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, place config there, set env (`XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, optionally `HOME`), run loader, assert loaded file came from `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tool/config.yaml` and not `~/.config/tool/config.yaml`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When an environment variable with the `TOOL_` prefix conflicts with a key in the config file, the environment variable value is used.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real bug surface is precedence in merged configuration across modules (file parser + env decoder + merge logic). Unit-testing merge in isolation can miss prefix/key-path translation issues.","test_description":"Write config file with a known value (e.g., `database.host: file-host`), set `TOOL_DATABASE_HOST=env-host`, run loader, assert effective config uses `env-host`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the config file contains a YAML syntax error, the error message includes the line number where the problem was detected.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on real YAML parser exception data and app-level error formatting. Mocking parser errors can always pass while missing real line-number extraction/propagation bugs.","test_description":"Create invalid YAML with a known syntax break on a specific line, run loader, assert failure message contains that line number from parser diagnostics.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the config directory does not exist at startup, the loader creates it and writes a defaults file before proceeding.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is filesystem side effects plus loader flow control. In-process mocks can hide path, mkdir, and write-order bugs; local real fs is needed. No external system/API needed.","test_description":"Start with an empty temp home/config root where target config dir is absent, run startup loader, assert directory now exists, defaults file is created at expected path, and loader proceeds without fatal error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
